1
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:16,875
I have been waiting eagerly.
For the bright, chilly sky.

2
00:00:16,958 --> 00:00:20,833
For the freezing wind. For the
fluttering, white snowflakes.

3
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:27,208
It has to be more than just
an ordinary snow, though.

4
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:32,500
It has to be something special.

5
00:00:32,583 --> 00:00:35,791
A snow that's surprising,
almost miraculous.

6
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:41,333
Yes. Like soft, powdery snow
on Christmas Eve, for example.

7
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:47,083
Weather lady! Weather
lady! Will it snow on

8
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:52,083
