18
00:02:51,291 --> 00:02:53,625
Yeah, and maybe it's also
the reason we haven't decided

19
00:02:53,708 --> 00:02:55,500
what to do after we graduate.

20
00:02:55,583 --> 00:02:58,958
Hey! Good point! Which means
the horrible grade I got

21
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:01,166
on my finals was obviously...

22
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:04,916
No question. Totally
the solar storm's fault.

23
00:03:08,541 --> 00:03:11,125
Oh, my. What is this
place? Hello, excuse me!

24
00:03:11,208 --> 00:03:12,791
Is anybody there?

25
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:16,791
Guys, it's a ghost! A ghost
in my pad! What do I do?

26
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:18,458
Airi?

27
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:21,791
Yeah, it's her. She's been
acting pretty strange lately.

28
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:24,208
She doesn't usually do this.
I don't think she's ever tried

29
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:27,875
to start a conversation
with anyone but me until now.

30
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:31,375
Do you think this is because
of the solar storm, too?

31
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:37,416
Okay, solar storm, GTFO!

32
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:40,291
Being responsible means
not blaming things on others.

33
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:42,708
Keep your spirits high.
We'll get through this!

34
