107
00:08:20,916 --> 00:08:23,458
Did you see that, Airi?
It was awesome!

108
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:26,083
I must've surfed that wave
for five whole seconds!

109
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:29,291
Fun! Now, would you like to hear
tomorrow's weather forecast?

110
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:32,208
The Tanegashima Region
can expect clear skies.

111
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:37,875
Gezi. Hey, what the--?

112
00:08:38,916 --> 00:08:42,750
Will you please stop poking me
like that. It doesn't feel good.

113
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,291
'Kay, sorry. But I
really want to know

114
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:45,875
the flag completion status.

115
00:08:45,958 --> 00:08:50,291
Right! Airi is on
the case! Let's see. Oh!

116
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:53,000
It looks like the final
flag has just been cleared!

117
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:56,250
The AR annotation
has been made visible!

118
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:59,583
Let's hurry up and find it!
Quick, it's going to snow!

119
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:04,208
Snow is falling, falling
down. Snow is falling.

120
00:09:04,291 --> 00:09:08,291
December 23rd. The day
before Christmas Eve.

121
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:10,791
Yhe day Airi might've
disappeared for good.

122
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:15,416
That was the day I finally
found Kimijima Report Number 6.

123
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:19,333
Utilizing the media to
disseminate fabrication as

124
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:23,250
reality is already an
outdated method of persuasion.

125
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:26,208
Rather, twenty-first
century propaganda will

126
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:29,833
function by augmenting
fantasy into reality.

127
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:32,916
Why do these things have to be
so complicated and confusing?

128
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,708
They make my head hurt.
All right, Report Number 7

129
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:38,250
should be the final one.
What are the flags?

130
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:42,250
Leeet's seeee. In order
to access Report Number 7,

131
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:44,583
all six previous reports
need to be unlocked.

132
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,125
And that's all!

133
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:48,250
Wait, so that's it?
No missions to complete

134
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,750
like with the other ones?

135
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:52,875
Apparently not. It sounds
like it's been made visible now

136
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:55,375
but unfortunately,
I don't know where it is.

137
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:57,375
Man. Gimme a break.

138
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:04,083
Umm. Airi would really like to
go back to her home now, please.

139
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:10,750
Airi's birthday is tomorrow!
Airi wants to go home

140
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:14,541
for her birthday and Christmas
Eve. Would that be okay?

141
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:17,208
Wait, hold on. You were
programmed to have a birthday?

142
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:18,625
That's unusual.

143
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:21,083
Not really "programmed."
But Christmas Eve was the day

144
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:24,416
Airi first woke up, so
it's sort of like a birthday.

145
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:26,833
Oh. Okay, well, in that case,

146
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:29,125
what was programmed
as your home?

147
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:32,291
It isn't programmed!
It's really Airi's home!

148
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:35,666
It's the actual place where
Airi and her master lived!

149
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:39,666
We have to go to
Kimijima's place. Really?

150
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,083
It's completely falling apart.

151
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:59,875
Is that how you see it?
For Airi, it's still as nice

152
00:10:59,958 --> 00:11:03,291
and tidy as she remembers
it being nine years ago.

153
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:05,791
So it is.

154
00:11:09,416 --> 00:11:13,458
There's something about
this room. It seems familiar.

155
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:16,750
My master was an amazing
person! So sweet and kind!

156
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,833
Sometimes Airi would
cook for him as a way of

157
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:21,833
saying "thank you." That's
what this room was for.

158
00:11:21,916 --> 00:11:23,416
I don't know how
that would work.

159
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:26,333
I've never heard of
an AI cooking before.

160
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:36,750
A basement?

161
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:39,791
Down there is where my
master has his work room.

162
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:50,916
Look at that.

163
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:56,875
It's just like the door in the
old museum. Which should mean.

164
00:11:57,875 --> 00:11:59,208
Hidden Hand.

165
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:17,875
What does this machine do?

166
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:21,083
There should be some buttons
there. Do you see them?

167
00:12:40,916 --> 00:12:43,416
Airi, what--?
I-I don't understand!

168
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:48,125
I haven't seen her in a long
time. Her name is Airi Yukifune.

169
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:50,458
She is the original Airi.

170
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,416
The original?

171
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:58,541
It's untreatable. That's what
the doctors said. "Untreatable."

172
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:01,750
My illness is serious, though
not actually life-threatening,

173
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,875
but I would suffer greatly
for the rest of my life.

174
00:13:04,958 --> 00:13:06,958
That's what they said, anyway.

175
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,083
Eventually, I found the only
thing I ever looked forward to

176
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,916
was the weather forecast.

177
00:13:17,916 --> 00:13:20,625
As I lay there, I told myself
that if a miracle happened

178
00:13:20,708 --> 00:13:24,541
and our southern island had snow
on Christmas Eve, then maybe,

179
00:13:24,625 --> 00:13:28,208
just maybe, I would
miraculously get better, too.

180
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:33,041
So as the end of December
rolled around every year,

181
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:35,833
I'd watch the weather
forecast a dozen times a day,

182
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:38,666
sighing every time
they predicted sunshine.

183
00:14:07,083 --> 00:14:08,916
That's when I
met Kou Kimijima.

184
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,291
The man who would
become Airi's master.

185
00:14:13,375 --> 00:14:15,916
He knew all about my
illness and how sick I was.

186
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,833
So one day he gave me
the most wonderful present.

187
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:21,000
It was something he was
working on at the time.

188
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:22,958
Something incredible.

189
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:25,541
He gave me an
alpha version of IRUO.

190
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:29,916
With it, I got to travel to
places all around the world

191
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:30,958
and I could
talk to him about

192
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:33,083
all the exciting
adventures I had!

193
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,916
However, it wasn't long before
those pleasant days were

194
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,541
nothing more
than a nice memory.

195
00:14:50,416 --> 00:14:54,166
My illness steadily worsened and
I gave up the childish idea that

196
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,833
a miracle would happen
and I'd be healed.

197
00:14:59,458 --> 00:15:02,916
But when Kimijima
found this out, he said...

198
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,958
Oh, Airi, I'm so sorry.
But I think I may know a way

199
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:09,291
to make your wish
come true. However.

200
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:11,375
It would be very dangerous.

201
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:18,166
This is the
chamber you'll sleep in.

202
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,583
It will likely be
decades before you wake up.

203
00:15:20,666 --> 00:15:23,041
But when you do,
things will be different.

204
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:26,583
You'll wake to an era when your
illness has become curable.

205
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:31,333
Although, I'm sure you'll be
lonely sleeping all that time,

206
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:34,125
so I'll make sure
you're able to dream.

207
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:36,458
And that's when he
created the Airi you know.

208
00:15:36,541 --> 00:15:39,208
Inside IRUO.
My new dream world.

209
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:45,833
Good night for now,
my Sleeping Beauty.

210
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:49,458
Good night, Kimijima.
Thank you so much.

211
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,291
Sweet dreams, little one.

212
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,916
I went back and forth over it
for a long time, but I ended up

213
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,875
reporting the simple
truth to the police.

214
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:17,875
Time for tomorrow's weather
forecast. As usual for this time

215
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:20,916
of year, the Tanegashima region
will experience clear skies

216
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,875
and a zero percent
chance of precipitation.

217
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,416
Guess what Airi learned today.

218
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:29,125
"A kiss on a white Christmas
will make love blossom."

219
00:16:29,208 --> 00:16:31,583
That's what the
weather lady said, anyway.

220
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:34,583
