you? Are you in love?

224
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:44,041
Airi can't be in love. That
sort of thing isn't included

225
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:49,166
in her programming. But,
as a girl, it is interesting.

226
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,291
If it snows, will you.

227
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:53,458
What?

228
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:55,708
If a miracle does
happen, a kiss would be

229
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:59,125
a nice way to commemorate
it. Will you give me one?

230
00:17:11,541 --> 00:17:13,916
Well, that's it.
Merry Christmas Eve!

231
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:18,791
It looks like it isn't
going to snow after all, huh?

232
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:22,458
I did have my hopes up a
little. Even so, Airi still had

233
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,833
a very nice time in her dream.

234
00:17:24,916 --> 00:17:27,041
I'm so glad I got
to meet you, Brother.

235
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:30,125
Airi really loved
talking to you.

236
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:33,083
I'm glad we met, too, but
do you have to talk like that?

237
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,833
Like it's the end of
everything? It might not be.

238
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:37,291
There's still a chance
that whatever maintenance

239
00:17:37,375 --> 00:17:39,875
they're doing won't
erase you, ya know.

240
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:43,458
I guess that's true. But
still, since it never snows,

241
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:46,750
I gave up believing in
miracles a long time ago.

242
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:58,666
Snowflakes. Look,
Brother, it's snowing!

243
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:02,208
Airi can see it, too!
All white and soft!

244
00:18:12,291 --> 00:18:14,750
Looks like today's
weather report was wrong!

245
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:17,750
So now here's the
updated forecast for tonight!

246
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:20,083
In the Tanegashima
region, there will be...

247
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:22,833
...clear skies followed by snow!

248
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:25,708
Hey, Brother!

249
00:18:27,416 --> 00:18:29,791
You remember the
promise from earlier?

250
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:33,583
Promise? Wait! You
really want me to kiss you?

251
00:18:33,666 --> 00:18:35,791
I do! So, where
is it going to be?

252
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:37,375
On the forehead,
or on the cheek?

253
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:40,000
Or maybe it's on Airi's lips?

254
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,291
In case you're wondering,

255
00:18:43,375 --> 00:18:45,541
the forehead would
be Airi's first choice.

256
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,166
Are you serious?

257
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,750
Oh, no! You're not going to
break your promise, are you?

258
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:52,916
Just when it's
finally snowing, too.

259
00:19:21,125 --> 00:19:26,250
Brother. What's wrong?
Why is Airi crying like this?

260
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:31,125
I don't understand what's
happening. I don't feel sad.

261
00:19:32,958 --> 00:19:36,375
Who knows, maybe
it's another glitch.

262
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:40,416
If that's the case, then
I should thank my master.

263
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:44,250
Because this is one glitch
that Airi doesn't mind so much.

264
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:47,083
Thank you, Brother.

265
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,750
Having a crane
makes this a lot faster.

266
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:01,000
So what do you think?

267
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:02,375
Is the monopole motor
really going to work?

268
00:20:02,458 --> 00:20:04,583
Oh yeah! I'm totally fired up!

269
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:07,291
So, Yashio, what's the deal.
Have you tried calling for

270
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:10,125
Airi since they finished
the maintenance on IRUO?

271
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:13,041
Why would I? There's
no point. She was erased.

272
00:20:13,125 --> 00:20:15,291
Well, why don't you
give it a try, anyway?

273
00:20:15,375 --> 00:20:18,041
Like right now, I mean.
What could it hurt?

274
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:22,083
Airi.

275
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:26,166
See? It's like
I said, she's gone.

276
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,458
They deleted her like
a virus from a hard drive.

277
00:20:28,541 --> 00:20:32,166
You're sure? But I could have
sworn I saw Airi just yesterday.

278
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,375
Really? Well if so,
then why didn't she

279
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:35,875
show up when I called her?

280
00:20:35,958 --> 00:20:37,666
Because she isn't here.

281
00:20:38,666 --> 00:20:41,166
Airi is gone.
The only one left is--

282
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,750
It's Gezi!

283
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:46,500
Yes. Accordingly, there will be
some changes to our interaction.

284
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:49,583
There is no need to
touch, no need to tap,

285
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:52,583
and certainly no need to
kiss me on the forehead.

286
00:20:53,666 --> 00:20:56,041
Kiss your forehead? But.

287
00:20:56,875 --> 00:20:59,041
Hold on a second! You
actually remember that?

288
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,541
I am not sure. It is
not immediately clear why

289
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:05,541
Gezi referred to you kissing
her on the forehead just now.

290
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:08,791
A check is underway to search
for any possible viruses.

291
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:14,083
Well, I couldn't say if it's
a virus or not, but either way

292
00:21:14,166 --> 00:21:17,000
it's perfectly all right with
me. I know this is a little

293
00:21:17,083 --> 00:21:21,416
late, but Merry Christmas to
you, Gezi, and to Airi, too.

294
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:24,625
And the same to you,
Yashio. Merry Christmas.

295
00:22:58,166 --> 00:23:01,333
Gunbuild 2 is finally
on the way to completion.

296
00:23:01,416 --> 00:23:05,583
A Monopole motor-drive system.
A laser-based power supply.

297
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:07,875
Despite the many
obstacles to be faced,

298
00:23:07,958 --> 00:23:10,416
Aki is excited about
the upcoming expo,

299
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:13,625
but what tragedy will occur
when Mizuka confronts Kai

300
00:23:13,708 --> 00:23:16,916
while he searches for yet
another Kimijima Report?

301
00:23:19,041 --> 00:23:20,458
Episode 16.

302
00:23:20,541 --> 00:23:21,916
Let's hit it off everybody!

303
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,625
Later days!

